.\" shlib - A shell library of reusable functions
.TH SHLIB_ARRAYS 3 "January 2026" "shlib 0.1.2" "Shell Library"
.SH NAME
shlib_arrays \- Array manipulation functions from the shlib library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B source
.I /path/to/shlib.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shlib_arrays
provides functions for working with Bash arrays.
Requires Bash version 3 or higher.
.PP
.B Note:
Array functions take the array variable
.I name
as an argument (without the $ prefix), not the array contents.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.SS Length
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_len " array_name"
Output the number of elements in the array named
.IR array_name .
.SS Modification
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_append " array_name element..."
Append one or more elements to the array.
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_delete " array_name index"
Delete the element at
.I index
from the array. Remaining elements are re-indexed.
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_pop " array_name"
Remove the last element from the array.
.SS Ordering
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_sort " array_name"
Sort the array in place (lexicographic order).
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_reverse " array_name"
Reverse the array in place.
.SS Output
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_print " array_name" " [separator]"
Print array elements on one line joined by
.I separator
(default: space).
.TP
.BI shlib::arr_printn " array_name"
Print array elements one per line.
.SH EXAMPLES
Get the length of an array:
.PP
.RS
.nf
#!/usr/bin/env bash
source /path/to/shlib/shlib.sh

my_array=(apple banana cherry)
count=$(shlib::arr_len my_array)
echo "Array has $count elements"  # Array has 3 elements
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
All functions return 0.
